{"id":14881389,"mediaExerciseId":"cb9dc8b1-9f09-4214-83b7-a5f0fc2e134c","exerciseName":"2","chapterName":"13","chapterTitle":"Return, Risk, and The Security Market Line","groupId":612375,"groupTitle":"Critical Thinking Questions","isPremium":true,"sectionName":null,"sectionTitle":null,"pageNumber":450,"solutions":[{"id":5991632,"modifiedOn":"2021-01-01T00:00:00.000000","steps":[{"columns":[{"text":"In this exercise, we are asked to evaluate the market returns. ","images":{"latex":{"large":{"height":28,"srcUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/22/01/07/f9c24b63030facde192125ae738ef3a2/d462b75f55cb0f43e7d14f5e086bb31e/lateximg_large.png","width":808},"regular":{"height":15,"srcUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/22/01/07/f9c24b63030facde192125ae738ef3a2/d462b75f55cb0f43e7d14f5e086bb31e/lateximg.png","width":403}},"additional":null},"hasInvalidKatex":false,"isTextOnly":true}],"isResult":false,"stepNumber":1},{"columns":[{"text":"The **announcement** describes a shift in stock prices or price fluctuations that occurs as a direct consequence of a statement.","images":{"latex":{"large":{"height":68,"srcUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/22/01/07/f9c24b63030facde192125ae738ef3a2/e2fbaef5a57736470898ddc297126833/lateximg_large.png","width":996},"regular":{"height":34,"srcUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/22/01/07/f9c24b63030facde192125ae738ef3a2/e2fbaef5a57736470898ddc297126833/lateximg.png","width":497}},"additional":null},"hasInvalidKatex":false,"isTextOnly":false}],"isResult":false,"stepNumber":2},{"columns":[{"text":"Suppose the government announces that the economy's growth rate is expected to be 2% in the next year based on a recently completed study. In that case, security prices will remain unchanged due to this statement since the growth rate is accurately foreseen.\n\n\n\nThis is due to the fact that the announcement has no real value for the investors; in this case, the investors accept it as aÂ confirmation.","images":{"latex":{"large":{"height":141,"srcUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/22/01/07/f9c24b63030facde192125ae738ef3a2/1b5b427a639414bb1edd4a6abf9e3eb4/lateximg_large.png","width":1020},"regular":{"height":72,"srcUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/22/01/07/f9c24b63030facde192125ae738ef3a2/1b5b427a639414bb1edd4a6abf9e3eb4/lateximg.png","width":511}},"additional":null},"hasInvalidKatex":false,"isTextOnly":false}],"isResult":false,"stepNumber":3},{"columns":[{"text":"However, if the economy had anticipated the announcement of the 2% growth rate, it would make a difference because it would mean that the 2% growth rate is in addition to the 5% growth rate for the previous year.\n\nThis announcement implication has the ability to generate significant price shifts in securities. As a result, the 2% will almost certainly raise security prices since the announcement will encourage investors to purchase securities.","images":{"latex":null,"additional":null},"hasInvalidKatex":false,"isTextOnly":false}],"isResult":false,"stepNumber":4},{"columns":[{"text":"To conclude, if investors take the announcement as confirmation or the growth rate is precisely forecasted, **the announcement will stay unaltered.**\n\nOn the other hand, if the announcement is only an estimate rather than a specific forecast, **security prices may increase or decrease depending on the circumstances.**","images":{"latex":{"large":{"height":174,"srcUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/22/01/07/f9c24b63030facde192125ae738ef3a2/e4fb95af15bae6aef5bb9b042d86826a/lateximg_large.png","width":1007},"regular":{"height":89,"srcUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/22/01/07/f9c24b63030facde192125ae738ef3a2/e4fb95af15bae6aef5bb9b042d86826a/lateximg.png","width":503}},"additional":null},"hasInvalidKatex":false,"isTextOnly":false}],"isResult":false,"stepNumber":5}],"rating":5,"solutionUuid":"a62518ed-b12e-493d-8c6f-bac8963e1be4","editorVersion":2,"answeredOn":null,"ratingCount":null,"solutionOrder":null,"totalSteps":5}],"textbook":{"authors":"Bradford D. Jordan, Randolph W. Westerfield, Stephen A. Ross","imageUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/textbook_covers/tmpm0p82b7h","imageThumbnailUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/cache/d1/d3/d1d34d106dd29dd2e71be582412ef59d.jpg","id":34320,"isbn":"9781259918957","isPremium":true,"title":"Fundamentals of Corporate Finance","edition":"12th Edition","verifiedSolutionCount":1217,"shouldBeIndexableForSeo":true,"modified":1665448474394,"active":true,"publisher":"McGraw-Hill Education","mainTextbookIsbn":null,"subjects":{"level1":["Social Science"],"level2":["Economics"],"level3":["Finance"]}},"nextExercises":[{"id":14881390,"exerciseName":"3","page":450,"hasSolution":true,"mediaExerciseId":"05b6ce32-c931-4a4c-adc9-2bae7f7e65c1","_webUrl":"https://quizlet.com/explanations/textbook-solutions/fundamentals-of-corporate-finance-12th-edition-9781259918957/chapter-13-critical-thinking-questions-3-05b6ce32-c931-4a4c-adc9-2bae7f7e65c1"},{"id":14881391,"exerciseName":"4","page":450,"hasSolution":true,"mediaExerciseId":"bb52d383-fffc-4c9f-a944-9f621f8263f1","_webUrl":"https://quizlet.com/explanations/textbook-solutions/fundamentals-of-corporate-finance-12th-edition-9781259918957/chapter-13-critical-thinking-questions-4-bb52d383-fffc-4c9f-a944-9f621f8263f1"}],"previousExercises":[{"id":14881388,"exerciseName":"1","page":450,"hasSolution":true,"mediaExerciseId":"a0666abd-9420-4465-8459-d443924df4dc","_webUrl":"https://quizlet.com/explanations/textbook-solutions/fundamentals-of-corporate-finance-12th-edition-9781259918957/chapter-13-critical-thinking-questions-1-a0666abd-9420-4465-8459-d443924df4dc"}],"_webUrl":"https://quizlet.com/explanations/textbook-solutions/fundamentals-of-corporate-finance-12th-edition-9781259918957/chapter-13-critical-thinking-questions-2-cb9dc8b1-9f09-4214-83b7-a5f0fc2e134c"}